---
name: prefer-arrow-functions
description: Prefer arrow functions unless named functions are required or preferred by a library
alwaysApply: true

---

# Overview

Always prefer arrow functions unless named functions are required or preferred by a library.

## Example scenarios of named functions being required

1. Function overloading with TypeScript.
2. Functions that require an external `this` binding.

## Example scenarios of named functions being preferred

1. Functional components in React. These are functions that return JSX in .tsx files. They shuold always be named, NOT arrow.
2. Cache libraries using function names for keys
